	{{> blog1_p text="Restoring degraded ecosystems is vital for biodiversity conservation. This includes the restoration of forests, aquatic ecosystems, and other biomes, which helps increase species populations and restore their habitats. Using native species in restoration ensures more resilient and locally adapted ecosystems." }}

